---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import FormulaBuilder from '../components/FormulaBuilder.astro';
const sections = [
  'about', 'kernel', 'identities', 'parameters', 'seam', 'regimes',
  'structural', 'composition', 'fixed-points', 'builder', 'expressions', 'reference'
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Formula Builder — GCD" description="Complete formula reference and interactive expression builder for the GCD kernel.">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

    <!-- ═══════════ HERO ═══════════ -->
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-2">Formula Reference &amp; Builder</h1>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-lg italic">Algebra est cautio, non porta. &mdash; The algebra is a warranty, not a gate.</p>
      <p class="text-kernel-500 text-sm mt-2 max-w-3xl">
        The complete formula structure of the GCD kernel &mdash; from the four primitive equations
        through the algebraic identities, frozen parameters, seam budget, regime gates, and
        53 structural identities. Every formula derives from Axiom-0. The interactive builder
        at the bottom lets you evaluate any expression live.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══════════ NAV ═══════════ -->
    <nav class="mb-8 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      {sections.map(s => (
        <a href={`#${s}`} class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium
          bg-kernel-800/60 text-kernel-400 hover:text-kernel-200 hover:bg-kernel-700/60
          border border-kernel-700/40 transition no-underline">
          {s.replace(/-/g, ' ').replace(/\b\w/g, c => c.toUpperCase())}
        </a>
      ))}
    </nav>

    <!-- ═══════════ §1: ABOUT ═══════════ -->
    <section id="about" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Formula Structure</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400 mb-4">
        The kernel function K&nbsp;:&nbsp;[0,1]<sup>n</sup>&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;&Delta;<sup>n</sup>&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;(F,&nbsp;&omega;,&nbsp;S,&nbsp;C,&nbsp;&kappa;,&nbsp;IC) takes a trace vector
        <span class="text-kernel-300">c&nbsp;&isin;&nbsp;[0,1]<sup>n</sup></span> and weights
        <span class="text-kernel-300">w&nbsp;&isin;&nbsp;&Delta;<sup>n</sup></span>
        and produces 6 outputs from 4 primitive equations + 2 derived values,
        with only <span class="text-cyan-400 font-bold">3 effective degrees of freedom</span> (F, &kappa;, C).
        S is asymptotically determined by F and C.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">4 Primitive Equations</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            F (fidelity), &kappa; (log-integrity), S (entropy), and C (curvature) are computed
            directly from the trace vector. They form the irreducible core of the kernel.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">2 Derived Values</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            &omega;&nbsp;=&nbsp;1&nbsp;&minus;&nbsp;F (drift) and IC&nbsp;=&nbsp;exp(&kappa;) (integrity composite)
            are derived algebraically. They participate in the immutable identities.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">3 Effective DOF</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            The statistical constraint S&nbsp;&asymp;&nbsp;f(F,&nbsp;C) reduces 6 outputs
            to 3 independent degrees of freedom: F, &kappa;, C. As n&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;&infin;,
            corr(C,&nbsp;S)&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;&minus;1.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §2: KERNEL PRIMITIVES ═══════════ -->
    <section id="kernel" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Kernel Primitives</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-kernel-500 mb-4 italic">Tier-1 &mdash; immutable by construction. The mathematical function and its provable properties.</p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <!-- F -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">F</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Fidelity <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(fidelitas)</span></h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-green-300 overflow-x-auto">
                F = &Sigma; w<sub>i</sub> c<sub>i</sub>
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                Weighted arithmetic mean of the trace vector. Measures what survives collapse.
                Range: [0, 1]. Tag: <span class="text-kernel-500 font-mono">K-F</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- kappa -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">&kappa;</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Log-Integrity <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(log-integritas)</span></h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-cyan-300 overflow-x-auto">
                &kappa; = &Sigma; w<sub>i</sub> ln(c<sub>i,&varepsilon;</sub>)
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                Logarithmic sensitivity of coherence. Guard band &varepsilon;&nbsp;=&nbsp;10<sup>&minus;8</sup> prevents pole.
                Range: &le;&nbsp;0. Tag: <span class="text-kernel-500 font-mono">K-&kappa;</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- S -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">S</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Bernoulli Field Entropy <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(entropia)</span></h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-amber-300 overflow-x-auto">
                S = &minus;&Sigma; w<sub>i</sub> [ c<sub>i</sub> ln c<sub>i</sub> + (1&minus;c<sub>i</sub>) ln(1&minus;c<sub>i</sub>) ]
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                Entropy of the collapse field. Computed, but not free &mdash; asymptotically
                determined by F and C. Maximized at the equator c&nbsp;=&nbsp;&frac12;. Range: &ge;&nbsp;0. Tag: <span class="text-kernel-500 font-mono">K-S</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- C -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-purple-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">C</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Curvature <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(curvatura)</span></h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-purple-300 overflow-x-auto">
                C = stddev(c<sub>i</sub>) / 0.5
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                Coupling to uncontrolled degrees of freedom. Normalized standard deviation.
                Range: [0, 1]. Tag: <span class="text-kernel-500 font-mono">K-C</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- omega -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4 border-l-2 border-l-red-700">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">&omega;</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Drift <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(derivatio)</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-600 ml-2">derived from F</span></h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-red-300 overflow-x-auto">
                &omega; = 1 &minus; F
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                How much is lost to collapse. Collapse proximity measure. Range: [0, 1]. Tag: <span class="text-kernel-500 font-mono">K-&omega;</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- IC -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4 border-l-2 border-l-blue-700">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">IC</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Integrity Composite <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(integritas composita)</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-600 ml-2">derived from &kappa;</span></h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-blue-300 overflow-x-auto">
                IC = exp(&kappa;)
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                Multiplicative coherence &mdash; weighted geometric mean. Integrity cannot exceed fidelity:
                the limbus integritatis IC&nbsp;&le;&nbsp;F. Range: (0, 1]. Tag: <span class="text-kernel-500 font-mono">K-IC</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Delta -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/50 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-yellow-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg w-10 shrink-0">&Delta;</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Heterogeneity Gap</h3>
              <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-yellow-300 overflow-x-auto">
                &Delta; = F &minus; IC &ge; 0
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
                Measures channel heterogeneity. Zero when all channels are equal (rank-1). Large
                when one channel is near dead (geometric slaughter). Taylor: &Delta;&nbsp;&asymp;&nbsp;C&sup2;/(8F).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §3: ALGEBRAIC IDENTITIES ═══════════ -->
    <section id="identities" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Algebraic Identities</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-kernel-500 mb-4 italic">Three identities always hold by construction. One statistical constraint tightens with n.</p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <!-- AI-1 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-kernel-900 to-kernel-900/80 border border-green-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-green-600 bg-green-900/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">AI-1</span>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Duality Identity <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(complementum perfectum)</span></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-3 my-2 font-mono text-base text-green-300 text-center">
            F + &omega; = 1
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Exact to machine precision &mdash; verified to 0.0e+00 residual across 10,000 traces.
            In Fisher coordinates: sin&sup2;&theta;&nbsp;+&nbsp;cos&sup2;&theta;&nbsp;=&nbsp;1.
            <span class="text-kernel-600 italic">Tertia via nulla</span> &mdash; no third possibility.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- AI-2 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-kernel-900 to-kernel-900/80 border border-cyan-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-cyan-600 bg-cyan-900/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">AI-2</span>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Integrity Bound</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-3 my-2 font-mono text-base text-cyan-300 text-center">
            IC &le; F
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            The solvability condition: for n&nbsp;=&nbsp;2, the trace recovery
            c<sub>1,2</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;F&nbsp;&plusmn;&nbsp;&radic;(F&sup2;&nbsp;&minus;&nbsp;IC&sup2;)
            requires IC&nbsp;&le;&nbsp;F for real solutions. Equality iff all c<sub>i</sub> are equal.
            Derived independently from Axiom-0. <span class="text-kernel-600 italic">Limbus integritatis.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- AI-3 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-kernel-900 to-kernel-900/80 border border-blue-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-blue-600 bg-blue-900/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">AI-3</span>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Log-Integrity Relation</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-3 my-2 font-mono text-base text-blue-300 text-center">
            IC = exp(&kappa;)
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Definition link between &kappa; and IC. Bridges multiplicative (IC) and additive (&kappa;) coherence.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- SC-1 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-kernel-900 to-kernel-900/80 border border-amber-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber-600 bg-amber-900/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">SC-1</span>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200">Entropy Determination <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal">(statistical constraint)</span></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-3 my-2 font-mono text-base text-amber-300 text-center">
            S &asymp; f(F, C) &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; corr(C, S) &rarr; &minus;1 as n &rarr; &infin;
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Reduces 6 kernel outputs to 3 effective degrees of freedom. CLT-based &mdash;
            tightens with channel count. S is computed but not free.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §4: FROZEN PARAMETERS ═══════════ -->
    <section id="parameters" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Frozen Parameters</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-kernel-500 mb-4 italic">
        Seam-derived, not prescribed. The unique values where seams close consistently across all 23 domains.
        <span class="text-kernel-600">Trans suturam congelatum</span> &mdash; same rules both sides.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-xs">
            <thead>
              <tr class="text-kernel-500 border-b border-kernel-700">
                <th class="text-left p-2">Symbol</th>
                <th class="text-left p-2">Value</th>
                <th class="text-left p-2">Role</th>
                <th class="text-left p-2">Why This Value</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-kernel-400">
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-green-400">&varepsilon;</td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">10<sup>&minus;8</sup></td>
                <td class="p-2">Guard band / &varepsilon;-clamp</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Pole at &omega;=1 does not affect measurements to machine precision</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-green-400">p</td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">3</td>
                <td class="p-2">Exponent in &Gamma;(&omega;)</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Unique integer where &omega;<sub>trap</sub> is a Cardano root of x&sup3;&nbsp;+&nbsp;x&nbsp;&minus;&nbsp;1&nbsp;=&nbsp;0</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-green-400">&alpha;</td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">1.0</td>
                <td class="p-2">Curvature cost: D<sub>C</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;&alpha;&middot;C</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Unit coupling</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-green-400">&lambda;</td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">0.2</td>
                <td class="p-2">Auxiliary coefficient</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Return-rate adaptation speed</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-green-400">tol<sub>seam</sub></td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">0.005</td>
                <td class="p-2">|s| &le; tol for PASS</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Width where IC &le; F holds at 100% across all 23 domains</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-cyan-400">c*</td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">0.7822</td>
                <td class="p-2">Logistic self-dual fixed point</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Maximizes S&nbsp;+&nbsp;&kappa; per channel; solves ln((1&minus;c)/c)&nbsp;+&nbsp;1/c&nbsp;=&nbsp;0</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-cyan-400">&omega;<sub>trap</sub></td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">0.6823</td>
                <td class="p-2">Trapping threshold</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">Cardano root of x&sup3;&nbsp;+&nbsp;x&nbsp;&minus;&nbsp;1&nbsp;=&nbsp;0</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono text-cyan-400">c<sub>trap</sub></td>
                <td class="p-2 font-mono">0.3177</td>
                <td class="p-2">Channel trapping threshold</td>
                <td class="p-2 text-kernel-500">c<sub>trap</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;1&nbsp;&minus;&nbsp;&omega;<sub>trap</sub></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §5: SEAM BUDGET ═══════════ -->
    <section id="seam" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Seam Budget</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-kernel-500 mb-4 italic">
        The seam is the verification boundary between outbound collapse and demonstrated return.
        The budget must reconcile &mdash; residual &le; tol.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">&Gamma;(&omega;) &mdash; Drift Cost</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-red-300 overflow-x-auto text-center">
            &Gamma;(&omega;) = &omega;<sup>p</sup> / (1 &minus; &omega; + &varepsilon;)
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Simple pole at &omega;&nbsp;=&nbsp;1 with effective residue 1/2. Convex on [0, 1&minus;&varepsilon;) for p&nbsp;&ge;&nbsp;2.
            At &omega;<sub>trap</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;0.6823, &Gamma;&nbsp;=&nbsp;1 exactly &mdash; single-step escape becomes impossible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">D<sub>C</sub> &mdash; Curvature Cost</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-purple-300 overflow-x-auto text-center">
            D<sub>C</sub> = &alpha; &middot; C
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">Linear curvature penalty. &alpha;&nbsp;=&nbsp;1.0 (unit coupling).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">&Delta;&kappa; &mdash; Conservation Budget</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-cyan-300 overflow-x-auto text-center">
            &Delta;&kappa;<sub>budget</sub> = R &middot; &tau;<sub>R</sub> &minus; (D<sub>&omega;</sub> + D<sub>C</sub>)
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">Credit (return) minus debits (drift + roughness). The ledger must reconcile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Seam Residual</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-yellow-300 overflow-x-auto text-center">
            s = &Delta;&kappa;<sub>budget</sub> &minus; &Delta;&kappa;<sub>ledger</sub> &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; |s| &le; tol<sub>seam</sub> for PASS
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Budget identity minus observed log-integrity change. Sequential seam deltas telescope (L-20):
            &Sigma;<sub>i</sub>&nbsp;&Delta;&kappa;<sub>i</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;&kappa;(t<sub>n</sub>)&nbsp;&minus;&nbsp;&kappa;(t<sub>0</sub>).
            Forms a monoid &mdash; associative with identity, error&nbsp;5.55&times;10<sup>&minus;17</sup>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Cost Elasticity</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2 my-2 font-mono text-sm text-orange-300 overflow-x-auto text-center">
            &varepsilon;<sub>&Gamma;</sub> = &omega;(3 &minus; 2&omega;) / (1 &minus; &omega;)
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Effective critical exponent for budget blowup. Approaches 4 near the pole.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §6: REGIME GATES ═══════════ -->
    <section id="regimes" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Regime Gates</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-kernel-500 mb-4 italic">Four-gate criterion. Derived from gates, never asserted. Gate precedence: CRITICAL &rarr; COLLAPSE &rarr; WATCH &rarr; STABLE.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-green-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-green-400">Stable <span class="text-kernel-600 font-normal ml-1">12.5% of Fisher space</span></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="text-xs font-mono text-green-300 space-y-1">
            <p>&omega; &lt; 0.038</p>
            <p>F &gt; 0.90</p>
